Crown Princess Mathilde of Belgium, Crown Prince Felipe and Crown Princess Letizia of Spain, Queen Anne Marie and King Constantin of Greece appear on the Lejonbacken Terrace after their wedding ceremony on June ... more Image 39 of 39 If the crown fits: Kate, other royals rock the tiara 1 / 39 Back to Gallery Kate Middleton, aka Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge, is known for her modern fashion choices, but it was an antique addition to her wardrobe that got everyone's attention.
Kate wore the Lotus Flower crown to her first state banquet, which honored Chinese President Xi Jinping and his wife Peng Liyuan at Buckingham Palace on Tuesday. The crown once belonged to the Queen Mother and was rumored to be Princess Margaret's favorite headpieces.
RELATED: Photos: Young, rich and royal
The rare occasion marked the third such time Kate has worn a crown, the first being the Cartier Halo tiara at her 2011 wedding to Prince William and the Lotus Flower Tiara for the Queen's diplomatic reception in 2013.
Crowns and tiaras have long since been a the symbol of royalty, with some monarchs choosing all diamonds, while others opt to add rich-colored gems or pearls throughout.
Take a look at the gallery above to see other queens and princesses donning their tiaras.
Which is your favorite? Tell us in the comments section below.
